How to transfer all Python Packages from pip to Anaconda (conda) in Windows?

Here's the solution:
1. Enter in cmd:

pip freeze

Output:
agate==1.6.1
agate-dbf==0.2.1
agate-excel==0.2.3
agate-sql==0.5.4
aiofiles==0.4.0
aiohttp==3.6.2
alabaster==0.7.12
ansi==0.1.3
anvil==0.0.2
appdirs==1.4.3
...

2. Create requirements.txt

3. If you are using Windows enter in cmd:

FOR /F "delims=~" %f in (requirements.txt) DO conda install --yes "%f" || pip install "%f"

